CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1946, pg. 22, reads: "Rising Star - Fritz Reiner, conductor of the Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra, commands Miss Carol Brice for her renditions of a difficult program of music by Mahler and de Falla at the Syria Mosque last week. Dr. Reiner predicts a brilliant future for the young contralto. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Symphony conductor Fritz Reiner, shaking hands with contralto Carol Brice, in Syria Mosque
